<subSubSection id="C37F6512FF94FFE9FF4C2D4DC78A28B3" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF94FFE9FF4C2D4DC78A28B3" blockId="9.[151,1437,1286,2031]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis id="B911EA8BFF94FFE9FF4C2D4DC72328EB" bold="true" box="[199,321,1394,1419]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D1AFF94FFE9FC012D4DC20628EA" box="[906,1124,1394,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Macrolygistopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EA8BFF94FFE9FC012D4DC20628EA" box="[906,1124,1394,1418]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Macrolygistopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the pronotum subtrapezoidal, with anterior and lateral margins stout and pronounced and by the entire elytra bluish black, iridescent, distally broadened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6512FF94FFEAFF4C2DE1C5E32D98" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="331" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF94FFE9FF4C2DE1C5842BCB" blockId="9.[151,1437,1286,2031]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis id="B911EA8BFF94FFE9FF4C2DE1C7162897" bold="true" box="[199,372,1502,1527]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">Redescription.</emphasis>
Head black, with rostrum as long as antennomeres I+II (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF94FFE9FB962DE1C2172897" box="[1053,1141,1502,1527]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1433,1456]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,198,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,193,1413]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Rostrum: 10. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 11. M. quadricostatus; 12. M. caeruleus; 13. M. germaini; 14. M. grandjeani; 15. M. subparallelus; 16. M. testaceirostris; 17. M. simoni; 18. M. kirschi. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271308/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FBDD2DE0C2172897" box="[1110,1141,1503,1527]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
); coronal suture shallow; median interocular distance of 
<date id="FFDB1059FF94FFE9FE762E3CC47A2B7B" box="[509,536,1539,1563]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FE762E3CC4682B7B" box="[509,522,1539,1563]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
the width of eyes. Mandibles slightly arched, testaceous. Maxillary palp with palpomeres III+IV as long as II; palpomere I small, about half the length of II; palpomere IV securiform, broadened compared to others. Antennae finely pubescent, scape long, tubular, as long as III; antennomere II small, 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FF1C2E51C6C32BE7" box="[151,161,1646,1671]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FF202E51C6D82BE7" box="[171,186,1646,1671]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="6.0">6</number>
of antennomere I length; antennomere III subequal to I in length; antennomeres IV and V subequal, length of 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FA0D2E50C3F02BE7" box="[1414,1426,1647,1671]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FF1C2EACC6C72BCB" box="[151,165,1683,1707]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="4.0">4</number>
of antennomere III; antennomeres V to XI gradually decreasing in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF94FFE9FF4C2E88C7762A5B" blockId="9.[151,1437,1286,2031]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">
Pronotum subtrapezoidal, transverse, wider than longer (
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FCE92E88C5102BAF" box="[866,882,1719,1743]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FCFD2E88C5F12BAF" box="[886,915,1719,1743]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="11.0">11</number>
), orange testaceous, with margins stout and pronounced, and median black stripe; a pair of longitudinal elevations parallels, constrict at basal and apical third, broadened in middle third; with a pair of oblique elevations in basal third region (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF94FFE9FBA12EC1C21F2A77" box="[1066,1149,1790,1815]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1260,1283]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,200,1229]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,193,1239]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Pronotum: 19. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 20. M. quadricostatus; 21. M. caeruleus; 22. M. germaini; 23. M. grandjeani; 24. M. simoni; 25. M. subparallelus; 26. M. testaceirostris. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271309/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="330">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF94FFE9FBD52EC0C21F2A77" box="[1118,1149,1791,1815]" pageId="9" pageNumber="330" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
